威肯說道[[勞·凱利|勞·凱利]]、[[麥可·傑克森|麥可·傑克森]]及[[王子_(音樂家)|王子]]做為它主要的靈感來源。<ref>{{cite web|last=Scott|first=Damien|date=2013-07-15|url=http://ca.complex.com/music/2013/07/weeknd-interview-cover-story|title=The Weeknd: Kiss And Tell (2013 Cover Story)|publisher=[[Complex_(magazine)|Complex]]|accessdate=2015-06-09|archive-date=2015-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150614024520/http://ca.complex.com/music/2013/07/weeknd-interview-cover-story|dead-url=no}}</ref>他常說，麥可·傑克森的音樂及“[[Dirty_Diana|Dirty Diana]]”的歌詞讓他想成為一名歌手。<ref name="RSinterview"/>他也說他十分成功的演唱風格是受[[哈比沙人|哈比沙人]]歌手，例如{{le|Aster Aweke|Aster Aweke}}，的影響。<ref name="RSinterview"/>他從小聽各種音樂流派，包括[[靈魂樂|靈魂樂]]、{{le|Quiet storm|Quiet storm}}、[[嘻哈音樂|嘻哈音樂]]、[[放克|放克音樂]]、[[獨立搖滾|獨立搖滾樂]]、以及[[後龐克|後龐克樂]]。<ref>{{cite news|last=Roberts|first=Randall|date=2012-12-17|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2012/dec/17/entertainment/la-et-ms-weeknd-review-20121217|title=Review: Abel Tesfaye, a.k.a. The Weeknd, has hall smoldering|newspaper=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=2013-02-01|archive-date=2013-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130120024947/http://articles.latimes.com/2012/dec/17/entertainment/la-et-ms-weeknd-review-20121217|dead-url=no}}</ref>其他影響威肯的歌手及樂團還有[[Portishead|Portishead]]、{{le|強烈衝擊|Massive Attack}}、{{le|肯諾 (歌手)|Cam'ron|肯諾}}、[[艾莉娅|艾莉娅]]、{{le|迪·安傑羅|D'Angelo}}、[[The-Dream|The-Dream]]、{{le|史威茲·畢茲|Swizz Beatz}}、<ref>{{Cite web|title=Artist Influences for The Weeknd|url=http://www.mtv.com/artists/the-weeknd/related-artists/?filter=influencedBy|website=[[音樂電視網|MTV]]|accessdate=2016-06-25|archive-date=2016-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105151850/http://www.mtv.com/artists/the-weeknd/related-artists/?filter=influencedBy|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[史密斯_(樂團)|史密斯樂團]]、{{le|Bad Brains|Bad Brains}}、[[Talking_Heads|臉部特寫]]、以及{{le|DeBarge|DeBarge}}。<ref name="bruce">{{Cite web|title=The Weeknd's New Album Is Inspired by Bad Brains, Talking Heads and the Smiths|author=Calum Slingerland|work=[[Exclaim!|Exclaim!]]|date=2016-02-06|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/the_weeknds_new_album_is_inspired_by_bad_brains_talking_heads_and_the_smiths|accessdate=2016-09-06|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225173258/https://exclaim.ca/music/article/the_weeknds_new_album_is_inspired_by_bad_brains_talking_heads_and_the_smiths|dead-url=no}}</ref>

威肯的歌是「建立在一個模糊、朦朧的作品」，<ref name="Hoby"/>且以緩慢的[[速度_(音樂)|節奏]]為特色，<ref name="Cohen"/>隆隆的低音，及淒涼的回聲。<ref name="Mistry"/>威肯唱歌時會用[[假聲|假聲]]，<ref>{{cite web|last=Robbins|first=Winston|date=2011-12-07|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2011/12/rookie-of-the-year-2011/|title=Rookie of the Year: The Weeknd|publisher=[[Consequence_of_Sound|Consequence of Sound]]|accessdate=2013-01-06|archive-date=2013-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130112021827/http://consequenceofsound.net/2011/12/rookie-of-the-year-2011/|dead-url=no}}</ref>表現出懇求、渴望的語氣。{{le|J. D. Considine|J. D. Considine}}發現他「[[震音|顫抖的音色]]」與[[麥可·傑克森|麥可·傑克森]]很像，但是他寫道，他避開麥可·傑克森之「強勁的[[藍調|藍調]]基礎」，而用了更多[[阿拉伯音樂|阿拉伯]]式的裝飾音。<ref name="Considine"/>他的音樂融合在節奏藍調作品上不常見的[[音樂取樣|音樂取樣]]，包括[[龐克搖滾|龐克樂]]及[[另類搖滾|另類搖滾樂]]。<ref name="Considine">{{cite news|last=Considine|first=J. D.|authorlink=J. D. Considine|date=2012-11-17|url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/music/how-the-weeknd-became-rbs-next-big-thing/article5370329/|title=How The Weeknd became R&B’s next big thing|newspaper=[[The_Globe_and_Mail|The Globe and Mail]]|location=Toronto|accessdate=2013-01-19|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223955/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/music/how-the-weeknd-became-rbs-next-big-thing/article5370329/|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[Spin_(雜誌)|Spin雜誌]]》的Marc Hogan說，威肯的音樂取樣傾向於「作出搖滾評論家所贊同的元素，儘管通常這些已經展現出他的性威脅元素」，像是{{le|海灘小屋|Beach House}}、[[Siouxsie_and_the_Banshees|苏克西与女妖]]及[[艾莉婭|艾莉婭]]的音樂取樣。<ref name="Hogan">{{cite journal|last=Hogan|first=Marc|date=2012-10-26|url=http://www.spin.com/2012/10/the-weeknd-enemy-the-smiths/|title=The Weeknd Imbues 'Enemy' With the Smiths' Seductive Power|journal=[[Spin_(雜誌)|Spin]]|location=New York|accessdate=2013-01-19|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107223927/https://www.spin.com/2012/10/the-weeknd-enemy-the-smiths/|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[Pitchfork_Media|Pitchfork Media]]》的Ian Cohen寫道，時常與威肯共事的{{le|Illangelo|Illangelo}}及{{le|Doc McKinney|Doc McKinney}}說威肯是「最高級的節奏藍調模範」。<ref name="Cohen">{{cite web|last=Cohen|first=Ian|date=2012-11-13|url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/17280-the-trilogy/|title=The Weeknd: Trilogy|publisher=Pitchfork Media|accessdate=2013-01-06|archive-date=2012-11-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121115231057/http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/17280-the-trilogy/|dead-url=no}}</ref>在舞臺上，威肯透過有[[組曲|組曲]]特徵之{{le|舞臺搖滾|Arena rock}}審美觀重新詮釋他的數位化作品。<ref name="Mistry"/>

他情緒性、淒婉的歌詞時常表現出傷痛的感覺以及關於性、<ref name="Hoby"/>毒品及派對的題材。<ref name="Mistry"/>《[[衛報|衛報]]》的Hermione Hoby說威肯的歌曲是「沉醉的{{le|慢節奏舞曲|Slow jam}}」，更說他的歌曲表達出「派對是一種存在經驗，性則充斥著疏離感，每件事都流露出虛幻與不安」的意境。<ref name="Hoby"/>《衛報》的Paul MacInnes詮釋威肯的混音帶《Trilogy》：「它是一個派對、餘興派對及[[宿醉|宿醉]]的粗野軌跡。」<ref>{{cite news|last=MacInnes|first=Paul|date=2012-11-15|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2012/nov/15/the-weeknd-trilogy-review|title=The Weeknd: Trilogy – review|newspaper=The Guardian|location=London|at=section G2, p. 23|accessdate=2013-01-06|archive-date=2012-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121129113655/http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2012/nov/15/the-weeknd-trilogy-review|dead-url=no}}</ref>《{{le|Toronto Standard|Toronto Standard}}》的Anupa Mistry，觀察到他的混音帶是個「弱懦、恍惚的殭屍女的角色……她的腿在被用物質膠合之後心甘情願地分離，她漸漸構成一些威脅只有當威肯在失魂落魄及感到脆弱時。」<ref name="Mistry"/>威肯表示：[[勞·凱利|勞·凱利]]曾經提及「如果以優雅、性感的方式唱出庸俗、愚昧的歌詞是可以被大眾接受的」，這成為他作曲的元素之一，因此他對勞·凱利及一定程度的對[[王子_(音樂家)|王子]]感到尊敬。<ref>{{cite web|last=Morgan|first=Nakiya|date=2013-07-15|url=http://rapfix.mtv.com/2013/07/15/the-weeknds-kiss-land-album-captures-first-experiences-outside-of-toronto/|title=The Weeknd's Kiss Land Album Captures First Experiences Outside Of Toronto|publisher=MTV News|accessdate=2013-07-19|archive-date=2015-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151110063852/http://rapfix.mtv.com/2013/07/15/the-weeknds-kiss-land-album-captures-first-experiences-outside-of-toronto/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

一些記者認為威肯將節奏藍調音樂調色盤的擴大，讓[[獨立音樂|獨立音樂]]與[[電子音樂|電子音樂]]能具體的表現出來；他的作品被歸類為{{le|另類節奏藍調|Alternative R&B}}<ref>Billboard Staff. [http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/6813596/grammys-2016-preview-best-r-and-b-song-best-urban-contemporary-album-nominees-the-weeknd-dangelo-more "Grammys 2016 Preview: The Weeknd, D'Angelo and More Soulful Singers Nominated for Best R&B Song and Best Urban Contemporary Album"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/6813596/grammys-2016-preview-best-r-and-b-song-best-urban-contemporary-album-nominees-the-weeknd-dangelo-more |date=20210107223949 }}. ''[[Billboard_Magazine|Billboard]]''. 13 February 2016.</ref>（有時幽默地稱為PBR&B）。<ref name="Hoby"/>Anupa Mistry寫道：「他將會被未來的節奏藍調音樂界諂媚地稱讚——是因為他是一位黑人歌手，並不是因為他正在做量化的、死板板的節奏藍調。」<ref name="Mistry"/>[[AllMusic|AllMusic]]的Andy Kellman將他分類為一個「另類節奏藍調行為」。<ref name="Kellman">{{cite web|last=Kellman|first=Andy|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/the-weeknd-mn0002674162|title=The Weeknd – Music Biography, Credits and Discography|publisher=[[AllMusic|AllMusic]]. [[Rovi_Corporation|Rovi Corporation]]|accessdate=2013-01-06|archive-date=2012-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121117212325/http://www.allmusic.com/artist/the-weeknd-mn0002674162|dead-url=no}}</ref>在他創建自己的經紀公司前，威肯隱瞞他的身分和保持神秘的人格，並同時將混音帶在線上釋出。

